<TITLE> 'Halve Bangabandhu Bridge toll' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 7 (bdnews24.com)-- An organisation of northern people has demanded halving the toll at the Bangabandhu Bridge, gateway to the region, on the river Jamuna. Uttarbanga Janakalyan Samity (North Bengal Welfare Association) made the demand at a press conference at the National Press Club on Monday. Association secretary general Mohammad Mizanur Rahman said toll rate at Bangabandhu Bridge is 10-40 times higher than what other bridges charge in the country. "The rate must be reduced to 50 percent in the 2010-11 fiscal year budget," he said. Mentioning that there was a proposal to collect Tk 3500 crore invested in the bridge through toll over 25 years, he said Tk 3000 crore was already realised in last 13 years. Association acting president MA Hakim was also present. b
